Journalctl - Filtering Logs

The [prgm]journalctl[/prgm] command queries and displays logs from systemd's journal.

# Filter by time (relative, or absolute)
$ [prgm]journalctl[/prgm] [arg]--since[/arg] [arg-value]"1 hour ago"[/arg-value]

# Filter by boot
$ [prgm]journalctl[/prgm] [arg]-b[/arg]                     # Current boot only
$ [prgm]journalctl[/prgm] [arg]-b[/arg] [arg-value]-1[/arg-value]                  # Previous boot

# Filter by unit/service
$ [prgm]journalctl[/prgm] [arg]-u[/arg] [arg-value]nginx[/arg-value]             # Logs for specific unit

# Filter by priority
$ [prgm]journalctl[/prgm] [arg]-p[/arg] [arg-value]err[/arg-value]
$ [prgm]journalctl[/prgm] [arg]-p[/arg] [arg-value]warning[/arg-value]
